message.content:
Calidris virgata is a bird species belonging to the sandpiper family.
It typically measures around 19-20 cm in length.
Its plumage is highly variable, with some individuals sporting a dark brown back and others featuring a grayish-brown hue.
The underparts are pale with dark streaks.
The bill is relatively long, thin, and slightly curved downward.
It is commonly found in coastal wetlands and mudflats in North and South America during breeding season.
During non-breeding season, it migrates to tropical coastlines of South America.
